$interpreted: Tindoiimu: Hmm... Sophie said the last book I brought them was too confusing. She didn't understand it.
Tingko: Well it was all about Fog Sect mythology, right? I bet that kind of stuff would just go right over her head.
Tindoiimu: How about this one? It's mythology but the stories are for kids.
Tindoiimu: This is probably more accessible.
Tingko: You're being awfully nice to Sophie, Princess. I'm sure she appreciates it!
Tindoiimu: Sophie, she's... around the same age as my little sister.
Tingko: Ah...
Tindoiimu: I haven't seen her in so long... We've sort of grown apart.
Tindoiimu: But when we were kids we'd always be together, playing around.
Tindoiimu: But now, if I have to keep staying here...
Tingko: Do you miss home, Princess?

Tindoiimu: Hmm... I guess it doesn't really matter if I do or don't. We're here now...
Anyway, let's go see Sophie.
Tingko: Alright! Your disguise is all set!
Sophie: If you speak 'Oodumbars', 'Oodumbars' will open...
Ru-yi: Sophie, it's "Udumbara". U-dum-bara~
Sophie: Ugh, this is so hard to read. I'm just gonna call it Oodumbars...
Sophie: Look at that illustration, it's so beautiful... I wonder if the real tree is that beautiful.
Ru-yi: Hmm... I wish I could remember, but I left the east when I was really young...
Tindoiimu: No one knows when the Udumbara will flower—it's actually quite rare. Plus, only the Arbiter is allowed to see it, so...
Tindoiimu: —Ow!
Tingko: You're bleeding...
Sophie: You're bleeding!?
Tindoiimu: It's fine, just hurt for a second.
Sophie: We should still put some ointment on it, just to make sure!
Ru-yi: Sophie, your face got super red~ Hehe!
Sophie: Whatever! I'm just worried about Tim is all...
Tingko: You should let me handle the sewing, Tim isn't very good at it.
Sophie: I'm so sorry... I feel like I'm the cause of this...
Tindoiimu: No, I want to help you! This needlework is a bit difficult, but still kind of fun.
Ru-yi: Finished!
Tingko: Wow, that looks great! Ru-yi, you're really good at that!
Tindoiimu: It looks just like the picture. I'm a bit jealous.
Sophie: I bet this will score big points with the audience. They'll love it!
Ru-yi: You really think they'll like us just because we use some props from their own culture?
Tindoiimu: Well... It's tough to say for certain until you try.

Sophie: Yeah, Tim's right. It's better to try this than do nothing at all!
Better to try and fail than never try at all!
Hanbei: Oh? Prince Tim's here again, huh?
Sophie: Hanbei!
Tingko: Prince Tim?
Ru-yi: Hehe... Sophie's been all excited to see you, every day she keeps saying "I wonder if Prince Tim will come today~".
Sophie: R-Ru-yi!!
Hutchinson: It's because you seem so, well, magnificent... and you always have your servant with you. So Sophie thinks you might be a prince.
Hanbei: I think Sophie reads too many storybooks.
Ru-yi: So, are you a prince, Tim?
Tindoiimu: Uh, well... you guys can think whatever you want.
Sophie: ......
Ru-yi: Aw, now I'm super curious! Can you tell us, please~
Tingko: I'd love to tell you, but I think we've really got to be going.
Tingko: Sir, it's time...
Tindoiimu: Yeah, I know.
Tindoiimu: We'll be going now. I'll be back again soon.
Sophie: O-Okay! Thank you so much for all of your help!
Tindoiimu: Don't mention it... How about you all tell me some stories of your travels next time?
Sophie: Of our travels? Ah... sure! Of course!
Ru-yi: Wow, Tim has such beautiful clothes...
Ru-yi: And he's so mysterious... doesn't tell us anything about himself! I bet he's a prince from the Kingdom of the Sun!
Hutchinson: He definitely has a gentlemanly vibe about him, if I don't say so myself.
Hutchinson: But he always leaves in such a hurry. I bet his family is very strict!
Hanbei: Hmm... Why would a prince from the Kingdom of the Sun hang around with us? I bet he's just some rich kid from the east with nothing to do.
Hutchinson: Even if he's not a prince, he still must be from an important family...
Sophie: ......
Happy Kid: Mommy, look~ Those flowers are pretty!
Surprised Beast: Wow, what a fine job they've done sewing those Udumbara flowers!
Excited Beast: Just beautiful! I wish I could take one home for my wife!
Sophie: Thank you, everybody! We're Morgan's Marvelous Circus! We'll be here performing tomorrow, the day after tomorrow, and the day after that, too!
Tindoiimu: There weren't many people today, but if word gets around I bet the crowd will get huge in no time.
Tingko: See, it's working! And Sophie even said they have plans to add even more cultural stuff later.
Sophie: Hey! What are you guys doing!?
Qilin Officer: You're breaking the law by performing here!
Qilin Officer: I order you take this all down immediately!
Sophie: Breaking the law!? But, we—
Sophie: Look! We have a permit!
Sophie: Check it out yourselves!
Qilin Officer: This permit is obviously fake! A lazy counterfeit, too! Come now, take it all down!
Tingko: You can't! What if you're discovered...!?
Tindoiimu: I can't let them push Sophie around like that! Don't worry, this disguise hasn't failed me yet!
Tindoiimu: (Damn, this disguise does limit my fighting style, though...)
Qilin Officer: This doesn't concern you, human!

Qilin Officer: They're trying to rebel! That's another violation! 
Drag 'em all away!
Tindoiimu: Their permit was fake...?
Tindoiimu: No way... Sophie wouldn't lie. There must be something fishy going on here...
Tingko: S-Sir, let me help, too!
